        <name>select</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_has_preset_ops::select</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Preset select callback. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This callback is called when the client requests to select preset identified by <computeroutput>index</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>index</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Preset index requested to activate. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>sync</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Whether the server must relay this change to the other member of the Binaural Hearing Aid Set.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 in case of success or negative value in case of error. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>-EBUSY if operation cannot be performed at the time. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>-EINPROGRESS in case where user has to confirm once the requested preset becomes active by calling <ref refid="group__bt__has_1ga2c0fe62baa63b72703d6f553f1de072b" kindref="member">bt_has_preset_active_set</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
